title: PPPP’s Makhdoom Fakhar Zaman wins PS-57 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP)’s Makhdoom Fakhar Zaman has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-57 Mitiari-II by securing 52,175 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Jalal Shah of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 44,873 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 52.80%.
